    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1102450446" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1102450446" />
    <a title="Kavita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5858699-kavita"><img alt="Kavita" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1315387023p2/5858699.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1102450446?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kavita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kavita" href="/user/show/5858699-kavita">Kavita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5858699-kavita?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5858699-kavita?shelf=uk">uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5858699-kavita?shelf=golden-age-mystery">golden-age-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1102450446" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9648069739753848550"><i>Mrs McGinty’s dead!<br/>How did she die?<br/>Down on one knee, just like I!</i><br/><br/>The title and the mystery is based on a British children&apos;s game. I&apos;ve never heard of it and apparently neither has Google. But it must have been pretty prevalent during Christie&apos;s time. This is yet another masterpiece from the Queen of Crime, featuring Hercule Poirot and Ariadne Oliver. I absolutely adore Mrs Oliver as a character and any book with her in it just shines for me. This case is also one of the only two cases in which P</span>
  <span id="freeText9648069739753848550" style="display:none"><i>Mrs McGinty’s dead!<br />How did she die?<br />Down on one knee, just like I!</i><br /><br />The title and the mystery is based on a British children's game. I've never heard of it and apparently neither has Google. But it must have been pretty prevalent during Christie's time. This is yet another masterpiece from the Queen of Crime, featuring Hercule Poirot and Ariadne Oliver. I absolutely adore Mrs Oliver as a character and any book with her in it just shines for me. This case is also one of the only two cases in which Poirot's life itself is threatened. The cheek of these murderers! <br /><br />Mrs McGinty is dead, and her lodger, James Bentley is arrested and convicted. He is about to hang soon but Superintendent Spence is not convinced in his guilt despite having been the one to have arrested him based on the evidence. He consults Poirot, who takes it up and begins to talk to all of Mrs McGinty's acquaintances. He realises that there is more to the case than meets the eye when he discovers a newspaper cutting about four erstwhile murderers or victims who have since disappeared from public eye. Who dun it?<br /><br />I loved the complete but seamless shift the novel takes from Mrs McGinty and James Bentley to a whole bunch of other characters. These two almost become secondary characters in their own book. The premise was a novel one and I loved how Mrs Oliver hit the nail on the head despite being wrong about the main murderer. The possible side murder case, left open-ended, is also a brilliant touch. All in all, a wonderful addition to the Poirot series.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9648069739753848550" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

